title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 6 §§ 210-3.2 - Reporting
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 6 §§ 210-3.2 - Reporting

State Regulations

Commencing with model year 2006, each manufacturer must
report, to the department, using the same format used to report this
information to CARB, New York sales data 90 days after the end of the model
year. During the engine manufacturer's production year, for each engine family, the engine manufacturer shall provide the commissioner within 45 days after the
last day in each calendar quarter the total number of personal watercraft
engines produced for sale in New York and their applicable
FEL(s). Notes
